This repo contains a list of java codes I am going to write and progress so that I can hone my coding skills!

Java Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA)
Welcome to my Java DSA repository! This repository serves as a personal sandbox and reference guide for implementing core data structures and solving algorithmic problems using Java.

Whether you are prepping for interviews, brushing up on fundamentals, or exploring efficient problem-solving techniques, this repo tracks my journey through the essentials of computer science.

🚀 Repository Structure & Topics Covered
The repository is organized by topic, moving from foundational data structures to advanced algorithmic paradigms.

📦 1. Data Structures
Arrays & Strings: Matrix manipulation, sliding window problems, two-pointer techniques.

Linked Lists: Singly, doubly, and circular linked lists.

Stacks & Queues: Implementations using arrays/linked lists, priority queues, and deques.

Trees: Binary Trees, Binary Search Trees (BST), AVL Trees, and Trie data structures.

Graphs: Adjacency matrix/list representations, BFS, and DFS traversals.

Hash-based Structures: Custom HashMaps and HashSets handling collision resolution.

🧮 2. Algorithms
Searching: Linear Search, Binary Search (and its variations).

Sorting: Bubble, Selection, Insertion, Merge, Quick, and Heap Sort.

Recursion & Backtracking: N-Queens, Subsets, Permutations, and Maze problems.

Greedy Algorithms: Huffman Coding, Fractional Knapsack, Activity Selection.

Dynamic Programming (DP): 0/1 Knapsack, Longest Common Subsequence (LCS), Coin Change, Memoization vs. Tabulation.

Graph Algorithms: Dijkstra's, Bellman-Ford, Kruskal's, and Prim's algorithms.